  "texts": [
    "This reveals that genes across all four populations responded differently to both pathogen challenge and R/S phenotype.To verify that our LFC cutoff did not bias interpretation of the results, we performed the same analysis on two subsets of our data.",
    "First, we examined the effect of using a traditional, adjusted p-value cutoff [99].",
    "We observed a larger proportion of DEGs that were unique to each population, for both pathogen treatment (Mean % unique = 55.3, SEM % unique = 14.9) and R/S phenotype (Mean % unique = 68.6, SEM % unique = 7.3).",
    "Second, we examined the effect of using different sized gene set cutoffs, ranging from 200 to 2000 genes.",
    "For each sample size, the proportion of DEGs that were uniquely expressed in each population ranged from 30 to 40%."
